<h2 id="ingedients">Ingredients</h2>
<ol>
    <li><input type="checkbox" /> 2 cups all purposes flavour</li>
    <li><input type="checkbox" /> 3 teaspoons baking powder </li>
    <li><input type="checkbox"/>half tea spoon salt</li>
    <li><input type= "checkbox"/>1 cup milk </li>
    <li><input type="checkbox"/> 1 egg</li>

    

</ol>
</main>
 
<h2 id="steps"> </h2>
<h4>Step1</h4>
<p>

 In a large bowl,  sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar 
 Make a well in the center and pour in the milk, egg and melted buter;
 mix until smooth

 </p>
 <h4>Step2</h4>
<p>
 Heat a lightly oiled griddle or frying pan over medium-high heat.
 Pour or scoop the butter onto the griddle, using approximately
 1/4 cup for each pancake.
 Brown both sides and serve hot.



</p>
